{
  "stem": "14897.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Out of 3 and 1/2 million of Jews in Poland, approximately 50,000 or so survived.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Obviously, that is not just quick wits.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That is a lot of luck.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It's a combination.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But you do have to have strengths.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Weak people did not survive.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And again, all this change is very abrupt.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In June of 1942, the Germans announced that the majority of the population of the ghetto of Warsaw-- not all of it, but the majority-- would be transported to what they said were working camps in the east.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And at the beginning, we really believed that this would be working camps, so much so that in the first few days, volunteers showed up to be moved, because people who had a very-- very difficult life in Warsaw, who couldn't make a living, who couldn't eat, the Germans would say, well, we will feed you.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You will work.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We will find work for you.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We will feed you, and life will be better.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "So for the first few days, there were actually volunteers.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "At the beginning, the idea was that only the people who were not employed by the Germans and their families would be transported.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And in the ghetto by that time, there were factories set up by the Germans, brush factories and textile factories primarily, where the Jews were working.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And those who worked had official papers, and they were supposed to be allowed to stay.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Gradually, of course, more and more of those people lost their papers and were transported out of the ghetto of Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "My father was a doctor in one such factory.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
